    <h2 id="login">1. Login & Authentication</h2>
    
    <h3>First-Time Access</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Visit <a href="https://retail.easycred.co.in" target="_blank">https://retail.easycred.co.in</a></li>
        <li>Enter your registered mobile number</li>
        <li>You'll receive an OTP (One-Time Password) via SMS</li>
        <li>Enter the OTP to authenticate</li>
        <li>Set up your password for future logins</li>
    </ol>
    
    <h3>Subsequent Logins</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Enter your registered mobile number</li>
        <li>Enter your password</li>
        <li>Click "Login" to access your dashboard</li>
    </ol>
    
    <div class="note">
        <strong>Note:</strong> If you forget your password, use the "Forgot Password" option to reset it.
    </div>

    <h2 id="dashboard">2. Dashboard Overview</h2>
    <p>After logging in, you'll see the main dashboard with:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Quick Stats:</strong> Summary of active loans, pending approvals, and collections</li>
        <li><strong>Recent Activity:</strong> Timeline of your recent actions</li>
        <li><strong>Notifications:</strong> Important alerts and messages</li>
        <li><strong>Quick Actions:</strong> Shortcuts to common functions</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="customers">3. Customer Management</h2>
    
    <h3>Adding a New Customer</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Navigate to "Customers" in the main menu</li>
        <li>Click "Add New Customer"</li>
        <li>Fill in customer details (name, contact info, KYC documents)</li>
        <li>Verify customer information</li>
        <li>Save the profile</li>
    </ol>
    
    <h3>Viewing Customer Details</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Go to "Customers"</li>
        <li>Search for the customer by name or ID</li>
        <li>Click on the customer to view:
            <ul>
                <li>Personal details</li>
                <li>Loan history</li>
                <li>Payment records</li>
                <li>Documents</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ol>

    <h2 id="loans">4. Loan Applications</h2>
    
    <h3>Creating a New Loan Application</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Navigate to "Loans" > "New Application"</li>
        <li>Select an existing customer or add a new one</li>
        <li>Choose loan product type</li>
        <li>Enter loan amount and tenure</li>
        <li>Upload required documents</li>
        <li>Submit for approval</li>
    </ol>
    
    <h3>Tracking Application Status</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Go to "Loans" > "Applications"</li>
        <li>View the status column for each application</li>
        <li>Click on any application for detailed status updates</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 id="popups">8. Enabling Pop-ups for EasyCred</h2>
    
    <div class="note">
        Some features like payment processing and document viewing require pop-up windows to function properly. Follow these instructions to enable pop-ups for EasyCred in your browser.
    </div>
    
    <div class="browser-instructions">
        <h3 class="browser-name">Google Chrome</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Click the <strong>lock icon</strong> (üîí) or <strong>warning icon</strong> (‚ö†Ô∏è) in the address bar</li>
            <li>Select <strong>"Site settings"</strong></li>
            <li>Under "Pop-ups and redirects," change from <strong>"Blocked"</strong> to <strong>"Allowed"</strong></li>
            <li>Refresh the EasyCred page</li>
        </ol>
        <p><em>Alternative method:</em></p>
        <ol>
            <li>Go to Chrome Settings (<code>chrome://settings/</code>)</li>
            <li>Click <strong>"Privacy and security"</strong> > <strong>"Site settings"</strong></li>
            <li>Select <strong>"Pop-ups and redirects"</strong></li>
            <li>Add <code>https://retail.easycred.co.in</code> to the "Allow" list</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    
    <div class="browser-instructions">
        <h3 class="browser-name">Mozilla Firefox</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Click the <strong>shield icon</strong> in the address bar</li>
            <li>Select <strong>"Turn off Blocking for This Site"</strong></li>
            <li>Refresh the page</li>
        </ol>
        <p><em>Alternative method:</em></p>
        <ol>
            <li>Go to <code>about:preferences#privacy</code></li>
            <li>Under "Permissions," find <strong>"Block pop-up windows"</strong></li>
            <li>Click <strong>Exceptions</strong> and add <code>https://retail.easycred.co.in</code></li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    
    <div class="browser-instructions">
        <h3 class="browser-name">Microsoft Edge</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Click the <strong>lock icon</strong> in the address bar</li>
            <li>Select <strong>"Permissions for this site"</strong></li>
            <li>Toggle <strong>"Pop-ups"</strong> to <strong>"Allow"</strong></li>
            <li>Refresh the page</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    
    <div class="browser-instructions">
        <h3 class="browser-name">Safari (Mac)</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Go to <strong>Safari</strong> > <strong>Preferences</strong> > <strong>Websites</strong></li>
            <li>Select <strong>Pop-up Windows</strong> in the left sidebar</li>
            <li>Find <code>retail.easycred.co.in</code> in the list and change to <strong>"Allow"</strong></li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    
    <h3>Troubleshooting Pop-up Issues</h3>
    <p>If pop-ups still don't work after enabling them:</p>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Clear your cache</strong>:
            <ul>
                <li>Chrome/Firefox/Edge: <code>Ctrl+Shift+Del</code> (Windows) or <code>Cmd+Shift+Del</code> (Mac)</li>
                <li>Select "Cached images and files" and clear</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Disable ad blockers/extensions</strong> temporarily:
            <ul>
                <li>Click the extension icon in your toolbar</li>
                <li>Pause blocking for <code>retail.easycred.co.in</code></li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Try incognito/private mode</strong> (often has fewer restrictions)</li>
        <li><strong>Check for browser updates</strong> (outdated browsers may have compatibility issues)</li>
    </ol>
    
    <div class="warning">
        <h3>Why EasyCred Needs Pop-ups</h3>
        <p>The platform uses pop-ups for:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Payment gateway windows</li>
            <li>Document previews</li>
            <li>OTP authentication screens</li>
            <li>Important system notifications</li>
            <li>Loan agreement signing</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h2 id="troubleshooting">9. Troubleshooting</h2>
    
    <h3>Common Issues & Solutions</h3>
    
    <p><strong>Login Problems:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Ensure you're using the correct mobile number</li>
        <li>Check your SMS for the latest OTP</li>
        <li>Reset password if needed</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p><strong>Application Errors:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Refresh the page</li>
        <li>Clear browser cache</li>
        <li>Try a different browser (Chrome recommended)</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p><strong>Connectivity Issues:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Check your internet connection</li>
        <li>Try switching between WiFi and mobile data</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>Contacting Support</h3>
    <p>For additional help:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Click "Help & Support" in the main menu</li>
        <li>Choose to:
            <ul>
                <li>Chat with support agent</li>
                <li>Submit a support ticket</li>
                <li>Call the support hotline (number provided in app)</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ol>
    
